Four Big Brother Naija, BBNaija housemates have been disqualified from participating in Head of House challenge The housemates were disqualified by Big Brother on Monday after they disobeyed rules of Head of House challenge. Biggie on Monday afternoon told housemates to play a puzzle of words. They were asked to form different words by picking one alphabet each from a bowl but four housemates disobeyed as they were caught selecting two alphabets from the bowl. Biggie after the challenge announced that Tacha, Mike, Diane and Venita disobeyed rules of the game, have been disqualified from Head of House challenge. DAILY POST recalls that Seyi emerged Head of House last week for the second time in a row. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.